Well it was Clarkes's - I was fourteen and - a girl - a girl name Parry, she was leaving and she st
arted in - in Clarkes' and she said they wanted - so I - I went down, stayed off school and went down for an interview and told them I was leaving and I left on the Tuesday night - I was fourteen. And - I always remember it, and me mother bought six bottl
es of lemonade and we father played the box. And we all - me - me friends, we all had a little party. There was no such a thing as cake or - we had the lemonade and we had the box and we sang.
