l I wouldn't - it'd last me two years that winter coat and I'd have a new dress or a new coat. I'll tell you one time what - what happened to me. I got Mr Lyons to give me - get me a nice costume and he brought me up and he measured me and I got the costu
m
e. Well I was just - it. And me mother brought me a pair of shoes and I was just - I was courting at the time. And you know I felt - I felt like two pounds a week in this outfit. And passing - - I'm passing Dunns, now you know Dunns in London Road, the ha
t
